<title>HONG KONG: India's IFCI sets US$75 mln loan.</title>
<headline>India's IFCI sets US$75 mln loan.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1996-10-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following syndicated loan issue was announced by arranger Sakura Finance Asia.</p>
<p> BORROWER   INDUSTRIAL FINANCE CORPORATION OF INDIA</p>
<p> AMOUNT     US$75 MLN    TYPE   TERM LOAN   MARGIN    6ML+70BP</p>
<p> MATURITY   TRANCHE (A) - 7 YRS WITH PUT OPTION IN YEAR FIVE,</p>
<p>		TRANCHE (B) - 6 YRS WITH AN AVERAGE LIFE OF 5 YRS</p>
<p> DRAWDOWN   MULTIPLE     AVAIL  45 DAYS     HOME CTRY INDIA</p>
<p>REPAYMENT  (A) BULLET  (B) FIVE SEMI-ANNUAL INSTALMENTS AFTER</p>
<p>		FOUR YEARS' GRACE PERIOD</p>
<p> REPLIES    22.OCT.96 (TENTATIVE)	     GOV LAW   ENGLISH</p>
<p> NOTES	PARTICIPANTS CAN JOIN EITHER TRANCHE.</p>
<p>ARRANGERS  ANZ LONDON, BANQUE PARIBAS AND SAKURA FINANCE ASIA MGT LEVELS AND FEES</p>
<p>   LEAD MGRS    US$7.5   MLN+ 50BP   ALL-IN  80</p>
<p>   SENIOR MGRS  US$5-7.4 MLN  45BP   ALL-IN  79</p>
<p>   MANAGERS     US$2-4.9 MLN  35BP   ALL-IN  77</p>
<p>--Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6960</p>
